<br>
----<br>
It is, with a heavy heart, that I write tonight to tell you all of the loss of someone special. On Tuesday night, &lt;Edited&gt;, the owner of our guild-mate Opaal Escense, died from a seizure in the hospital. She had Epilepsy, a condition that had her in and out of the hospital many times in the past.<br>
<br>
This loss comes as a complete shock and leaves me stunned without words to convey how truely wonderful she was. I would like to write here that the name &quot;Opaal Escence&quot; came from a company she owned and operated to train dogs to help people living with disabilities. She would more times then not sell these special animals to folks who really needed them for a small portion of their actual worth, because she was so kind to understand that these people truely needed these animals. While I have never had the gift of knowing her in person, I have shared countless hours online with her, and had countless conversations with her. She was someone who could completely turn my day around with her wonderful personality. The world is less for the loss of her. I hope we all can remember her as she was, someone very special.<br>
<br>
I ask that if any of you pray, no matter what diety you are, to please offer one up for &lt;Edited&gt;, owner of our friend and comrade Opaal Escence. <p><p><a href="http://jrwarton.home.mindspring.com/" target="_blank"><img src="http://jrwarton.home.mindspring.com/signatures/marilyna-sig.jpg" border="0" alt="Vist the Immortal Assailants Homepage"></a> <br>
